modules.description: Converts between S-expressions and time zone database representations, parsing and serializing time zone data. Works with `Sexplib.Sexp.t` and `Timedesc.Time_zone.Db.db` types. Used to load and persist time zone configurations from strings or S-expressions.

This module provides functions to convert date values to and from S-expressions, including direct string serialization and deserialization. It supports parsing and pretty-printing date values in S-expression format, handling both successful conversions and error cases. Concrete use cases include persisting date values to configuration files, transmitting date data in text-based protocols, and debugging date values in human-readable form.

This module provides functions to convert `Timedesc.Span.t` values to and from S-expressions, including direct string serialization and deserialization. It supports parsing and pretty-printing spans in S-expression format, enabling structured data interchange and configuration file handling. Use cases include persisting time spans to disk, transmitting them over a network, or embedding them in larger S-expression-based data structures.

Converts time zones to and from S-expressions and string representations. Works with `Sexplib.Sexp.t` and `Timedesc.Time_zone.t`. Used to serialize time zone data for storage or transmission, and to parse time zone identifiers like "America/New_York" into structured values.

Converts zoneless time values to and from S-expressions for serialization and parsing. Works with `Timedesc.Zoneless.zoneless` and S-expressions. Used to store or transmit time data without timezone information in a structured format.

Converts between S-expressions and time zone information structures. It supports parsing and serializing time zone data for storage or transmission. Useful when working with configuration files or APIs that require time zone metadata in S-expression format.

Converts between S-expressions and timestamp values. It supports parsing timestamps from S-expressions and serializing timestamps into S-expressions. This is useful when reading or writing timestamp data in configuration files or data interchange formats that use S-expressions.

This module provides functions to convert time values to and from S-expressions, including direct string serialization and deserialization. It supports the `Timedesc.Time.t` type, enabling precise time representation in S-expresssion-based data formats. Use cases include persisting time values in configuration files, transmitting time data across systems, and parsing time inputs from external sources.

This module implements S-expression serialization and deserialization for temporal data types including timestamps, dates, times, time spans, time zones, and zoneless time values. It provides direct conversions to and from S-expressions and string representations, supporting structured data interchange and configuration handling. Use cases include persisting time-based configurations, transmitting temporal data over text-based protocols, and embedding time values in S-expression documents.
